Context: Java development Kit > Other JDKs
Content: In addition to the most widely used JDK discussed in this article , there are other JDKs commonly available for a variety of platforms , some of which started from the Sun JDK source and some that did not . All adhere to the basic Java specifications , but often differ in explicitly unspecified areas , such as garbage collection , compilation strategies , and optimization techniques . They include :
Azul Systems Zing , low latency JDK for Linux ;
Azul Systems / OpenJDK - based Zulu for Linux , Windows , Mac OS X , embedded and the cloud ;
OpenJDK / IcedTea ;
GNU 's Classpath and GCJ ( The GNU Compiler for Java ) ;
Not being maintained or discontinued :
Apple 's Mac OS Runtime for Java JVM / JDK for Classic Mac OS
Blackdown Java -- Port of Sun 's JDK for Linux
Oracle Corporation 's JRockit JDK , for Windows , Linux , and Solaris ;
